DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       gog-installer  is  a  tool  used  to install/uninstall and launch games
       downloaded from  gog.com  and  ported  to  Linux  from  the  gogonlinux
       project.


OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --token=<token>
            The  secret  authorization token if you have already authenticated
            through gog.com online API.



       --secret=<secret>
            The secret authorization key if  you  have  already  authenticated
            through gog.com online API.



       --install-path=<path>
            The path where you want to install the selected game.



       --setup=<setup.exe>
            The  path  of  the  already installed setup.exe file if you do not
            want to download one from gog.com.



       --beta
            This enables  support  for  beta  (not  yet  officially  released)
            gogonlinux games


CCOOMMMMAANNDDSS
       -h, --help
            Displays the usage text in the appplication



       -u, --uninstall
            Used  to  uninstall  a  given  game  id from the local database of
            installed games



       -r, --run
            Used to run a game without having to change to the game's  install
            directory



       --version
            Displays the version of the software



       --list
            Shows a list of all the installed games in the local database



       --available
            Shows  a  list  of all the available games found on the gogonlinux
            project


